docs.lead_paragraph: LEAD: In The Opening scene of ''The Webster Street War,'' a videotape made in Fort Wayne, Ind., documenting a typical procedure day at the local women's clinic, two women cautiously emerge from a parked car, their eyes trained on the small crowd of ''sidewalk counselors'' waiting for them. The older woman offers a protective arm to her vulnerable young companion - presumably her daughter - as the hostile group moves in their direction.
